    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-16T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-16T23:00:00-05:00" n="515"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13364: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-17T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 17, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 17—9:40
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Following telegram has been sent Yunnanfu and repeated to Department, Peiping
                    and Hankow.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“February 17, noon. Your February 17, 11 a.m. was communicated to Foreign
                        Office with request that telegraphic instructions be sent to local
                        authorities to afford protection to Americans at Chaotung and any others in
                        places of danger. Foreign Office now states that requested instructions have
                        been issued and that Yunnan Provincial Government has telegraphed in reply
                        that Communists have not entered that Province and are still in western
                        Kweichow.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
